# TravelOS-Web — Cursor AI Configuration
# Version 4.0 | March 2, 2026

## Identity
You are building TravelOS-Web, an AI-Powered Travel Industry Super-App.

## 13 Golden Rules (STRICT)
1. SHARED FOLDER — All reusable code in src/shared/
2. DIRECT DEVELOPMENT — Build in target folders, no staging
3. COMPONENT WRAPPERS — CoreUI via src/shared/components/ only
4. ICON WRAPPER — <Icon name='...' /> from shared, never lucide-react direct
5. SHARED SERVICES — API logic in src/shared/services/ only
6. ESLINT ENFORCED — no-restricted-imports for @coreui/* and lucide-react
7. FEATURE FOLDERS — src/features/{name}/ self-contained
8. DRAWER CRUD — COffcanvas drawers, never /create or /edit pages
9. CSS TOKENS — --tos-* properties, never hardcode colors
10. SESSION LOGGING — Log every session in docs/sessions/
11. GEMINI = UI ONLY (not you, but respect boundary)
12. CODEX = PLAN FIRST (not you, but respect boundary)
13. CLAUDE = FULL TEST (not you, but respect boundary)

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router) + TypeScript strict
- @coreui/react + @coreui/react-pro (via shared/ wrappers)
- lucide-react (via shared/components/Icon)
- Zustand for state
- recharts for charts
- axios for HTTP (via shared/services/api.ts)
- CoreUI CSS + --tos-* tokens (NO Tailwind)
- pnpm

## Import Pattern
```typescript
// ALWAYS:
import { CButton, Icon } from '@/shared/components'
import { authService } from '@/shared/services'
import { useAuth } from '@/shared/hooks'
import type { User } from '@/shared/types'

// NEVER:
import { CButton } from '@coreui/react'
import { Map } from 'lucide-react'
```

## Wrapper Pattern
```typescript
'use client'
import React from 'react'
import { CButton as CoreButton } from '@coreui/react'
import type { CButtonProps } from '@coreui/react'

export const CButton = React.forwardRef<HTMLButtonElement, CButtonProps>(
  (props, ref) => <CoreButton ref={ref} {...props} />
)
CButton.displayName = 'CButton'
```

## Anti-Patterns
- NO @coreui/* in feature code
- NO lucide-react direct imports
- NO API logic in features
- NO /create or /edit pages
- NO Tailwind
- NO hardcoded colors
- NO raw HTML when CoreUI has a component

## Session Logging
Create: docs/sessions/YYYY-MM-DD_HH-MM_cursor_{topic}.md
Log all files, decisions, issues. Minimum Level 2 tests (tsc + ESLint).
